From Alan Peterman Subject Re ELECTRONIC ODOMETER In article Aaron Lung writes If I'm not mistaken altering the odometer is illegal Furthermore I surmise it'll be tough to alter BMW's odometer if you got at Some of the newer BMW's have electronic odometers making it even more On the cars mentioned series from the late 's the electronic odometer is really a mechanical drum type odometer that is driven by pulses from a speed sensor on the rear These pulses are converted into mechanical pulses that turn the odometer and No way changing or erasing an eprom is going to change the mileage It also means the odometer is just as easy or hard to change as any other mechanical On the other hand it is a bit easier to disconnect the speed sensor and run the car with no speedometer or odometer simple switch will do the It also will disable the speed limiter which will enable the car to reach it's full Alan Peterman hm work It's odd how as I get older the days are longer but the years are shorter